Cadence Capital Limited (ASX: CDM) has provided a daily buy-back update, reporting the purchase of 350,520 ordinary shares on 11 June 2025 for a total consideration of AUD 221,521.17, at prices ranging between AUD 0.6275 and AUD 0.63 per share. The company’s ongoing on-market buy-back, which began on 21 October 2024 and will run until 17 October 2025, has so far repurchased 4,529,415 shares out of a maximum target of 10 million, leaving 5,470,585 shares remaining under the program. The buy-back does not require shareholder approval.

FleetPartners Group Limited (ASX: FPR) provided a daily buy-back notification, reporting the purchase of 120,000 ordinary shares on 11 June 2025 for a total consideration of AUD 354,996, at prices ranging between AUD 2.92 and AUD 3.01 per share. The company has now bought back a cumulative total of 77,375,116 shares under its on-market buy-back program, which began on 10 May 2023 and is set to conclude by 23 January 2026, with an approved limit of 25 million shares post the January 2025 AGM. The buy-back is managed by Morgan Stanley Australia Securities.

Summary:

Clime Capital Limited (ASX: CAM) provided a daily update on its on-market share buy-back, noting that 100,000 ordinary shares were repurchased on 11 June 2025 at an average price of AUD 0.71355 per share, bringing the total bought back to 1,421,661 shares. The buy-back, managed by Sanlam Private Wealth, began on 10 March 2025 and will run until 9 March 2026, targeting a maximum of 15,055,408 shares (10% of issued shares). The highest price paid was AUD 0.755, and the lowest was AUD 0.675. No shareholder approval was required for the buy-back. The remaining shares to be repurchased stand at 13,633,747.

ClearView Wealth Limited (CVW) provided a daily buy-back notification on 12 June 2025, reporting the purchase of 200,000 ordinary shares on-market the previous day (11 June) for AUD 97,060, at prices ranging from AUD 0.48 to AUD 0.49 per share. The total shares repurchased to date under the ongoing buy-back program (which runs until 25 March 2026) are 9,802,500. While no fixed maximum has been set, the company aims to buy back up to 10% of its outstanding shares (657.7 million), with Morgans Financial Limited facilitating the transactions. The highest price paid historically was AUD 0.515, and the buy-back does not require shareholder approval.
